
given the state of what we have right now this seems like a reasonable first step

for an object 
{_id: xxxx, _rev: yyyy, attr1: xxxx, attr2: yyyy ....}

for collections of objects (ex: tasks)
{tasks: [{...}, {....}]}

for errors
{error: "conflict" reason: "xxkksks"}


conventions

enter create information
GET /users/new

create 
POST /users   application/text

query
GET /users/xxxx application/text | application/json

update
POST /users/xxxxxx  application/text | application/json
PUT /users/xxxxx

delete
DELETE /users/xxxxx application/json 


